# InstaEdit Frontend — Environment Variables
# Copy to .env and fill in your backend API URL.

# Backend API base URL (URL del server Go deployato)
# Per sviluppo locale: http://localhost:8080
# Backend API base URL.
# - LOCAL DEV:  http://localhost:8080  (the Fly dev backend, or `go run cmd/api`)
# - PRODUCTION: https://api.instaedit.org  (set in Vercel dashboard, NOT here)
#
# For PRODUCTION, the env var is set via the Vercel project dashboard
# (or `vercel env add` CLI) — see docs/DEPLOY.md §9 for the canonical
# setup. The build-time validation plugin (web/vite.config.ts →
# verifyApiBaseUrlPlugin) will FAIL the build if VITE_API_BASE_URL is
# missing or wrong for the target context (production requires an
# https URL, not http://localhost).
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080

# --- Demo mode (frontend-only preview when the Go backend is offline) ---
#
# Set to the literal string "true" to make the SPA run against mock data
# (see web/src/lib/demo.ts). When on:
#   • `authedFetch` and `fetchSession` return canned Responses (no network)
#   • A persistent "Demo mode" banner is shown at the top of every page
#   • Login form submit just navigates to /accounts as the demo user
#   • OAuth provider cards in /connections show a toast instead of
#     navigating to the (non-existent) backend OAuth URL
#   • The build validator skips the VITE_API_BASE_URL checks so you can
#     leave it empty/placeholder during the demo window
#
# Use cases:
#   • Fly.io payment is blocked and the API isn't deployed yet, but you
#     still want a navigable Vercel preview for screenshots / design review.
#   • Local dev without `go run cmd/api` running.
#
# When the backend is back online, REMOVE this env var (or set to
# "false") in Vercel → Project Settings → Environment Variables and
# redeploy. The SPA returns to the real network path with zero code
# changes — the demo-mode branches in auth.ts / Login.tsx / Connections.tsx
# are gated on `import.meta.env.VITE_DEMO_MODE === "true"` at build time.
#
# Any value other than the literal "true" is treated as off (e.g. "1",
# "TRUE", "yes", or unset all evaluate to false).
VITE_DEMO_MODE=false
